				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV>What do you think are the Paladin's top 5 best spells, discs, abilities, paladin-only items, or AA's of all time?&nbsp; Feel free to explain!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1)&nbsp; <STRONG>Instrument of Nife</STRONG> - 243 DD proc at level 30(26) was insane!&nbsp; For 5 plat from a VENDER.&nbsp; Heck you can't even buy DoD augs <EM>still to this day</EM> that proc that high.&nbsp; Subsequent upgrades are excruciatingly WEAK for the level obtained....just imagine if they had scaled in power /drool.&nbsp; Later in life we&nbsp;are required&nbsp;to plop down 50+ AA's to ever reach that kind of power again /rude</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2)&nbsp; <STRONG>Lay on Hands</STRONG> - the&nbsp;one single ability that has scaled in power since day 1, level 1 (though u need the accompanying AAs later in life).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3)&nbsp; <STRONG>Holy Steed</STRONG> - Seru bridle? bah! lets see them take that on a Corpse Run!&nbsp; Still to this day the best AA ever.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4)&nbsp; <STRONG>Deepwater Helm</STRONG> - free heals for the win!&nbsp; It pretty much peters out once you hit the mid 50's, but man it was nice to have around.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5)&nbsp; <STRONG>Ward of Tunare</STRONG> - gotta love this spell.&nbsp; Not too much help in high end zones, but makes lower/mid&nbsp;content soloable...and fun!</DIV>
				
